          }
        },
        "text": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>Rooted in the Japanese concept of shinogi – the ridgeline or backbone of a blade – SHINOGI systems are built with technical intent, shaped by real use, and refined through restraint. In traditional sword-making, the shinogi is not ornamental. It is essential. It provides strength, balance, and integrity. This philosophy is applied to every SHINOGI product, beginning with Case 15–25. Nothing is added without reason. Nothing exists without function. The result is equipment designed to endure time, movement, and daily wear.</p>"
          }
        }
